1000_Genomes_HighCov_autosomes.description: 1000 Genomes Project: The New York Genome Center (NYGC), funded by NHGRI, has sequenced 3202 samples from the 1000 Genomes Project sample collection to 30x coverage. Initially, the 2504 unrelated samples from the phase three panel from the 1000 Genomes Project were sequenced. Thereafter, an additional 698 samples, related to samples in the 2504 panel, were also sequenced.

CADD.description: Combined Annotation Dependent Depletion (CADD): an algorithm designed to annotate both coding and non-coding variants.

DANN.description: DANN: a deep learning approach for annotating the pathogenicity of genetic variants.

dbNSFP_variants.description: dbNSFP: a database developed for functional prediction and annotation of all nsSNVs in the human genome.

dbSNP.description: dbSNP: Reference SNP (rs or RefSNP) Hail Table. The database includes both common and rare single-base nucleotide variation (SNV), short (=< 50bp) deletion/insertion polymorphisms, and other classes of small genetic variations.

dbSNP_rsid.description: dbSNP: This Hail Table contains a mapping from locus/allele pairs to Reference SNP IDs (rsID). For the full dataset, see dbSNP.

gencode.description: GENCODE: aims to identify all gene features in the human genome using a combination of computational analysis, manual annotation, and experimental validation.

gerp_elements.description: GERP: identifies constrained elements in multiple alignments by quantifying substitution deficits.

gerp_scores.description: GERP: identifies constrained elements in multiple alignments by quantifying substitution deficits.

gnomad_hgdp_1kg_subset_dense.description: gnomAD: 1KG + HGDP subset, formatted as a dense MatrixTable. Samples included in this subset are drawn from the 1000 Genomes Project (n=2,435) and the Human Genome Diversity Project (n=780), which contain some of the most genetically diverse populations present in gnomAD.

gnomad_hgdp_1kg_subset_sparse.description: gnomAD: 1KG + HGDP subset, formatted as a sparse MatrixTable. Samples included in this subset are drawn from the 1000 Genomes Project (n=2,435) and the Human Genome Diversity Project (n=780), which contain some of the most genetically diverse populations present in gnomAD. Note: this version is formatted as a sparse MatrixTable.

gnomad_hgdp_1kg_subset_sample_metadata.description: gnomAD: Hail Table containing HGDP + 1KG gnomAD sample QC metrics, as well as additional sample metadata.

gnomad_hgdp_1kg_subset_variant_annotatio.description: gnomAD: Hail Table containing HGDP + 1KG variant annotations. Note that this Hail Table splits multi-allelic variants, so users who would like to annotate the sparse, unsplit MatrixTable with this Table will need to split the sparse MatrixTable first.

gnomad_variant_co-occurrence.description: gnomAD: Hail Table containing variant co-occurrence (inferred phasing) data for all pairs of variants within a gene where both variants have a global allele frequency in gnomAD exomes <5% and are either coding, flanking intronic (from position -1 to -3 in acceptor sites, and +1 to +8 in donor sites) or in the 5/3 UTRs. This encompasses 20,921,100 pairs of variants across 19,685 genes.

ldsc_baselineLD_annotations.description: LDSC Baseline-LD Model: contains 75 annotations (additional annotations included in later versions) including functional regions, histone marks, GERP scores, LD-related annotations of population genetics forces, MAF bins, and more.

ldsc_baselineLD_ldscores.description: LDSC Baseline-LD Model: contains 75 annotations (additional annotations included in later versions) including functional regions, histone marks, GERP scores, LD-related annotations of population genetics forces, MAF bins, and more. Represented as a matrix table whose columns are annotations and entries are the ld scores. For a table representation, see ldsc_baselineLD_annotations.
